{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"85c38ff3-f2fb-435b-8f06-c353a6fbbcca","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_018MW6kERhkfkNdoqx2EUdj1","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01K3k2ZyQb3iZAL8tZ6n9NJ5","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-00bc95512cb4402789c713d4c6638114 && dotnet nuget search xunit.v3 --take 5 2>/dev/null | head -30","description":"Search for xunit.v3 NuGet package version","initial_wait":15},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Search for xunit.v3 NuGet package version"}],"interactionId":"222428b8-a825-4bff-8465-69738ab06d30","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the migration from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **TestProject.csproj**: \n   - Replace `xunit` v2 package with `xunit.v3` package\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v3 doesn't use it - the test project becomes an executable)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed for v3)\n   - Change SDK to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` (stays the same, but need to add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`)\n   - The target framework can stay as net8.0\n\n2. **CustomAttributes.cs**:\n   - The using statement remains `using Xunit;` since `FactAttribute` and `TheoryAttribute` are still in the `Xunit` namespace in v3\n   - However, there are API changes to these attributes in v3 that I need to account for\n   \nLooking at the actual xUnit.net v3 migration:\n   - The NuGet package switches from `xunit` to `xunit.v3`\n   - The project needs to become an executable with `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`\n   - `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` and `xunit.runner.visualstudio` are no longer required\n   - `[InlineData]` continues to work as before\n   - `[Theory]` still exists as `TheoryAttribute`, just from the v3 package\n   - The test runner is now built-in and uses global usings or auto-generated entry points\n   - The `Assert` class and core testing attributes remain in the `Xunit` namespace\n\n, though some properties like `Skip` on `FactAttribute` may have shifted\n   - For `dotnet test` integration, I need to figure out whether `xunit.runner.visualstudio` still applies or if there's a v3-specific version I'm second-guessing myself on the specifics of xUnit v3's attribute system. The core migration steps are clear—swapping the package, removing the runner and SDK packages, and making the test project executable—but I'm less certain about how custom attributes that inherit from `FactAttribute` and `TheoryAttribute` behave in v3. The standard assertions like `Assert.True` and `Assert.NotNull` should still work, though I should verify the exact API changes for custom attribute constructors.\n\nLet me just start making the migration changes to the project file and see what breaks.\n\nUpdating the project file... I need to figure out how xUnit v3 handles test execution since it's an executable project rather than a traditional test library. The `global.json` configuration with the VSTest runner might need adjustment, though `dotnet test` should still work with the built-in runner. I'm trying to determine whether I need to keep that configuration or if it needs updating for v3's approach. I need to figure out the right test runner configuration for xUnit v3. The global.json's VSTest setting might not work with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so I should either update it to the correct runner or remove it entirely. Let me check what xUnit v3 versions are available and make the necessary adjustments.","outputTokens":2507,"requestId":"8052:1C3957:7475E3:7BAD2F:6A044D4F"},"id":"30568c52-c2bc-464d-8ea7-d41a37378480","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:08:00.564Z","parentId":"3aae7714-7623-4ef2-8379-f387e22952c9"}
